	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: MMC5 volume</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Apparently I was wrong about thinking I couldn't see the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/File:MMC5_audio.png" class="postlink">audio portion of the MMC5 PCB</a>. Can anyone with a MMC5 game that uses audio, or with an MMC5 game and a CopyNES, determine which signals are on pins 2 and 3? I suspect one's the pulse waves and the other's the DAC.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


